replies.body:
{{champion:41}} 
Oranges have a cast time, so always make sure you can survive long enough to finish eating them.
Also, he laughs when he ults.

{{champion:48}} 

Many people know that Trundle's Pillar of Ice has a small knockup when placed directly underneath a champion but when done while a champion is mid leap such as a Jax Q  or Lee Sin Q2 it will interrupt the leap and prevent the damage.  I find interrupting Jax's leap relatively easy because it has a shorter range making it more telegraphed and is a slower jump.  I get pretty psyched when I save someone from Lee Sin with the pillar because that's a lot more difficult since I play on 90 ping. 

Trundle's pillar can also be used to physically pin someone to a wall if you do it just right where it does not displace them significantly and you get the right angle.  It is really easy to avoid having this happen to you. It can only be done when you are hugging the wall really close.  I tend to get a lot of WTFs in chat from this one.
